Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal dysfunction (markedly elevated creatinine), proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with low blood glucose and HbA1c, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal). These findings suggest acute or chronic kidney injury, possible nephrotic syndrome, and metabolic derangements. Urgent clinical evaluation and nephrology referral are recommended.
